      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate VAD operating envelope including hematocrit, temperature, and blood analog rheology; full traceability to clinical operating conditions required.",
      "rationale": "Bench experiments used a glycerol-water blood analog rather than porcine blood; temperature was controlled but hematocrit equivalence was not verified across all five operating points. Achieved level 3 is below the required level 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty Uval) must be computed for hemolysis index at all five operating points with uncertainty bands from both simulation and experiment.",
      "rationale": "Comparison was performed at three of five operating points; experimental uncertainty was reported only as standard deviation without systematic bias characterization. Achieved level 3 does not satisfy required level 5."
